BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 740 Tm (Closing Notes) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 725 Tm (None of this is novel; it is the folklore written down so the next person does not have to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 710 Tm (reconstruct it from the code. The one non-obvious point is that reordered invalidations are) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 695 Tm (safe as long as versions are compared, never assumed.) Tj ET
